Installations:
--------------
1) Install community edition from confluent website
2) use the scripts in bin folder to  run it.[Windows folder contains windows bat script]


Steps:
-----
1) Start zookeeper: sudo sh bin/zookeeper-server-start ./etc/kafka/zookeeper.properties 
2) Start broker: sudo sh bin/kafka-server-start ./etc/kafka/server.properties
3) Create topic:

kafka-topics --create --topic test --partitions 1 --replication-factor 3 --bootstrap-server localhost:9092

4) Sending and reading it using kafka producer and consumer
kafka-console-producer --topic test --broker-list localhost:9092 < ../xyz.csv
kafka-console-consumer --topic test --broker-list localhost:9092 --from-beginning --group group1

5) Multinode[Same machine]: Create 3 copies of server.properties file as server-0.properties, server-1.properties, server-2.properties
Change the 
a) broker.id in server.properties
b) listeners = PLAINTEXT://:9093, ..9094 etc
c) log.dirs = /tmp/kafka-logs-0

Note: Number of partitions depend on storage requirement and parallel processing.


6) see log: /tmp/kafka-logs

kafka-dump-log --files /tmp/kafka-logs/stock-ticks-1/000200wqw.log
